In 1989 Sergio Vega replaces Alan Peters (ex-Agnostic Front bassist) in the New York hardcore band Absolution...
In 1990, Sergio Vega was instrumental in forming the new post-hardcore band Quicksand; at the time Vega was a prominent bassist of the genre.
Quicksand released their debut album, Slip, on February 9, 1993.
On February 28, 1995, Quicksand released their second album, Manic Compression.
The band reunited briefly in 1997 and toured with Deftones the next year.
In 1999, when Deftones bassist Chi Cheng was unable to perform onstage during a Deftones tour due to a toe surgery, Vega filled in for him on bass.
He released his first solo EP entitled The Ray Martin Sessions through the indie record label grapeOS in 2000.
On November 4, 2008, Deftones bassist Chi Cheng was seriously injured in a car accident in Santa Clara, California, and entered a coma-like state following the accident.
Deftones began writing a new album from scratch in June 2009 with Vega on bass.
The album, titled Diamond Eyes, was released on May 4, 2010.
In November 2012 the group released their second album with Vega, named Koi No Yokan.
In June 2012, Sergio and Quicksand would secretly reunite to play a surprise set at Revelation Records' 25th anniversary show.
This performance was followed by an appearance on the Jimmy Fallon Show as well as two sold out headlining shows at The Bowery Ballroom and The Music Hall of Williamsburg in August 2012.
In January 2013, Quicksand embarked on their first tour since the late 1990s.
They released their third album, Interiors, on November 10, 2017.
